args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor chapter 10 of the main campaign,\nas well as the ＂Dawn of Dragalia＂ event.
I'm ALBERIUS! If you're not afraid of my\nDRAGONBLOOD, then COME AT MEEE!
Come now, what are you doing?\nI said you could play outside AFTER\nyou finished cleaning your room!
Is Alberius not back yet, Mom?\nHe's still off fighting with Dad?
That's right. And if you clean your room\nand be a good boy, I'm sure they'll both\nbe back very soon.
But I haaaate cleaning my room...\nC'mon, everybody! Let's go play more!
Honestly! When the hero finally returns,\nI'm going to have him give that child\na stern talking-to.
Victory is ours! Let any who still do not\nfear the dragonblood step up and face me!
We can't take any more of this...\nRetreat! RETREAT!
We did it! We won the day!
I'm shocked at how easy it was to repel\nthe Dyrenell Empire! Three cheers for\nthe hero of the day, Alberius!

We were merely lucky our strategy played
out so well this time. And remember, our
war with the Empire isn't over yet. Let's
make sure we don't get complacent.

Ever with your own spoonful of humble pie,
eh, Alberius? C'mon, let's hurry back to the
village and tell everyone of our hero's
courageous deeds!
At a base and village allied with Alberius\nin South Grastaea...
But then, who should appear like a bolt\nfrom the blue, but the wielder of the\nsacred sword, the great Alberius!
As the mighty hero cut through wave after\nwave of enemies, the imperials all turned\ntail and ran like cravens!
All that to say, we kicked their tails\nfrom dusk to dawn! Bwaaa ha ha ha!
Your tale remains as gallant as the first\nthree times you told it today.

Oh, you know I will! Our hero Alberius is
the most amazing man I've ever met,
and I'm going to sing his praises until
my voice is gone!
Hah, you exaggerate, my friend.\nI'll never keep pace with the tales of my\nexploits if you continue those stories.

Do you see?! Alberius has achieved glory
beyond all measure, yet is humble as a
lamb in spring! Truly, he is the savior we
have all been waiting for!
Even the Other won't be able to stand\nagainst us with Alberius at our side!
I fear that may prove difficult.
All right, who's interrupting me\nin the middle of a story?!
That was I, good sir. I am an emissary of\nthe Faerie King himself, and come bearing\na message for the wielder of Dragalia.
O great hero Alberius! Our king beseeches\nyou to bring your sacred sword and might\nto our Faerie Kingdom!
The Faerie Kingdom? Yes, I remember\nhearing about that place from\nMidgardsormr at some point...

It is a kingdom in North Grastaea hidden
away from the world through magic.
Evidently, none may enter without
express permission of the faeries.
Wait, all the way up in North Grastaea?\nIt'd take ages to get there from here!
If your ultimate goal is to defeat the Other,\nyou may simply consider it a necessary\nexpenditure of time for the cause.
And if I make this trip to your kingdom,\nwhat will you do to aid our cause?
I am told our Faerie King will confer upon\nyou a secret rite which will permit you\nto defeat the Other.
I am but His Majesty's humble messenger,\nand not informed as to the particulars.
Then tell us what you DO know,\nas vague as it may be.
It is a rite known as the Blood Casket.
With it, anything can be sealed away.\nHowever, it is not a technique to be\nused by the fainthearted.

And to seal away a creature as strong
as the Other will take a person of
exemplary physical and mental ability—
a person much like you, Alberius.
However, once the Blood Casket is used,\nthe caster will suffer an endless agony\nakin to death itself—or so I am told.
I can guarantee the magic's effects are\ngreat enough to be worthy of the pain.
Thought you didn't know the details\nabout this, friend.

That is true—yet I know the Faerie King
body and soul, so believe me when I say
he is not the sort who would dispatch an
envoy to a foreign nation on a whim.

His position prevents him from easily
leaving our kingdom, but his feelings
of disgust for the Other's crimes are
quite the same as everyone's.
Yet with all due respect, feelings alone\nwill not deliver victory against the fiend.\nIf you would win, you must use the rite.

I have said all I came here to say,
and must now return to the kingdom.
And while hope you will see fit to
accompany me, I will not coerce you.
The rite is meaningless if you lack the\nwill to use it. The choice is up to you.
If your resolve to defeat the Other stands\nfirm, pray make your way to us anon.
Don't go, Alberius! If you leave,\nthe Empire will slaughter us!
Though the faeries claim there's no way\nto beat the Other without their rite, they\noffer no more than their words as proof.
I have fought and bled beside all of you,\nand I believe in the power of that bond\nfar more than some pretty talk!

We may lack this secret rite of theirs,
but if we combine our strength—all of
us—I know we can defeat the Other.
So put your trust in me and follow!
Is this truly the correct path, Alberius?

I told you, don't worry.
Er, and I hate to ask this, but could you
tell everyone to keep this business about
the faeries' secret rite to themselves?
I don't want to cause undue anxiety\nfor anyone else.
You worry too much, Midgardsormr.\nI'm just overheated from all the loud\ntalking. I'm going to get a little night air.
